name: Andrew Dai
title: Director
about: I am a third year Computer Science major with a minor in Sociology. After growing up outside Boston, I am almost always unsettled by Atlanta's warm weather. I am passionate about educational inequities and increasing access to Computer Science education.

name: Faizan Virani
title: Director
about: I'm a third year CS major and this is my second year on exec for HackGT. I enjoy hackathons and long walks on the beach. I'm a self-proclaimed professional musician and MC.

name: Lekha Surasani
title: Director of Finance, Director of Operations
about: I'm a computer science major at Georgia Tech from New Jersey. I'm passionate about helping others and promoting computer science education. I've worked at the NJ Department of Education, in the Office of Educational Technology, and in educational technology research labs. I also stay involved in Georgia Tech's community - aside from HackGT, I'm the President of Students Consulting for Nonprofit Organizations and Chair for the Honor Advisory Council at Georgia Tech.

name: Jordan Madison
title: Director of Communications
about: When people walk up to me, I want them to feel welcomed. I want for all their worries to go away in an instant because my purpose in life is to emit hope. To inspire others who can no longer hold their heads higher than their shoulders. In my eyes, I want people to see me as a beacon of light that inspires all to achieve the impossible.

name: Michael Eden
title: Director of Technology
about: A.B.C. Always Be Caring (about your contribution your community). (clearly) Going through my idealistic phase in both life and software. Talk to me about movies, music, skiing, surfing, stand up, improv, tv, biking, food, camping, and almost anything.
